Padziorno [padrn] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kostomoty, within roda lska County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland.[1] Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately 16 kilometres (10mi) south of roda lska, and 31 kilometres (19mi) south-west of the regional capital Wrocaw. Coordinates: 511N 1638E / 51.017N 16.633E / 51.017; 16.633
